I
 Steve Weinberger
 certify that:

I have reviewed this Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K of Inventure Foods
&nbsp;Inc.;

Based on my knowledge
 this Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K does not contain any untrue statement of a material fact or omit to state a material fact necessary to make the statements made
 in light of the circumstances under which such statements were made
 not misleading with respect to the period covered by this Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K;

Based on my knowledge
 the financial statements
 and other financial information included in this Annual Report
 fairly present in all material respects the financial condition
 results of operations and cash flows of the registrant as of
 and for
 the periods presented in this Annual Report;



Designed such disclosure controls and procedures
 or caused such disclosure controls and procedures to be designed under our supervision
 to ensure that material information relating to the registrant
 including its consolidated subsidiaries
 is made known to us by others within those entities
 particularly during the period in which this Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K is being prepared;

Designed such internal control over financial reporting
 or caused such internal control over financial reporting to be designed under our supervision
 to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles;

Evaluated the effectiveness of the registrant&#146;s disclosure controls and procedures and presented in this Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K our conclusions about the effectiveness of the disclosure controls and procedures
 as of the end of the period covered by this Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K based on such evaluation; and

Disclosed in this Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K any change in the registrant&#146;s internal control over financial reporting that occurred during the registrant&#146;s most recent fiscal quarter (the registrant&#146;s fourth fiscal quarter in the case of an Annual Report) that has materially affected
 or is reasonably likely to materially affect
 the registrant&#146;s internal control over financial reporting; and

The registrant&#146;s other certifying officer(s)&nbsp;and I have disclosed
 based on our most recent evaluation of internal control over financial reporting
 to the registrant&#146;s auditors and the audit committee of the registrant&#146;s board of directors (or persons performing the equivalent functions):

All significant deficiencies and material weaknesses in the design or operation of internal control over financial reporting which are reasonably likely to adversely affect the registrant&#146;s ability to record
 process
 summarize and report financial information; and

Any fraud
 whether or not material
 that involves management or other employees who have a significant role in the registrant&#146;s internal control over financial reporting.

 2015

Pursuant to 18 U.S.C. Section&nbsp;1350
 as adopted pursuant to Section&nbsp;906 of the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002
 each of the undersigned hereby certify
 in his capacity as an officer of Inventure Foods
&nbsp;Inc. (the &#147;Company&#148;)
 that
 to his knowledge:

The Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K for the period ended December&nbsp;27
 2014 of the Company (the &#147;Report&#148;)
 fully complies with the requirements of Section&nbsp;13(a)&nbsp;or 15(d)
 as applicable
 of the Securities of 1934
 and

The information contained in the Report fairly presents
 in all material respects
 the financial condition and results of operations of the Company.

   2015

		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Treasury Stock&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We record repurchases of our common stock
 $.01 par value (&amp;#x201C;Common Stock&amp;#x201D;)
 as treasury stock at cost.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We also record the subsequent retirement of these treasury shares at cost.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The excess of the cost of the shares retired over their par value is allocated between additional paid-in capital and retained earnings.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The amount recorded as a reduction of paid-in capital is based on such excess.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;The following unaudited pro forma consolidated results of operations (in thousands

		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;2.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;;font-size: 10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-indent:0pt;margin-left:0pt;padding:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:3pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;Acquisitions&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Sin In A Tin&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;On September&amp;nbsp;29
 2014
 we acquired the assets and intellectual property of a small boutique frozen desserts business
 Sin In A Tin
 for approximately $160
000 in cash. An additional amount of up to $0.5 million is payable to the seller in the form of an earn-out based on future net revenues from the Sin In A Tin products.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;At the time of acquisition
 the contingent consideration was recorded at $0.2 million based on the fair value assessment.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Additionally
 we recorded $0.1 million of identifiable intangible assets and $0.1 million of net tangible assets that were assumed as a part of this acquisition based on their estimated fair values
 and $0.2 million of residual goodwill.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;The above allocation will remain preliminary until the Company has all of the information necessary to finalize the allocation of the purchase price
 which shall be no later than one year following the acquisition date.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Fresh Frozen Foods&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;On November&amp;nbsp;8
 2013
 we acquired substantially all of the assets
 properties and rights of Fresh Frozen Foods
 a branded frozen vegetable processor.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;As consideration for the acquisition
 we assumed certain liabilities and obligations of Fresh Frozen Foods and paid an aggregate purchase price of $38.4 million in cash plus a working capital adjustment of $0.4 million.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;A portion of the purchase price was used to settle Fresh Frozen Foods&amp;#x2019; existing debt as of the closing of the transaction.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;An additional amount of up to $3.0 million could have been payable to Fresh Frozen Foods as contingent consideration in the form of an earn-out based on 2014 performance.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;At the time of acquisition
 the contingent consideration was recorded at $2.7 million based on the fair value assessment at acquisition.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Such contingent payment
 if any
 would be paid during the first quarter of 2015.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Acquisition costs of $1.1 million were incurred during the year ended December&amp;nbsp;28
 2013 and are included within selling
 general and administrative expenses.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The amount of net revenues attributable to Fresh Frozen Foods included in the consolidated statements of operations since the acquisition date were $8.9 million in fiscal 2013.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We do not allocate certain selling
 general and administrative expenses and therefore
 it is impracticable for us to separately identify earnings of the acquired entity since acquisition.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;

					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;text-align:right;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 12pt&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:02.68%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 12pt&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:01.30%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;$&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:11.56%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;text-align:right; nowrap=nowrap&gt;&lt;div style=float:left&gt;&lt;/div&gt;8
301
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:01.02%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 12pt&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Under the acquisition method of accounting
 the purchase price as shown in the table above is allocated to the tangible and identifiable intangible assets acquired and liabilities assumed based on their estimated fair values.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The excess purchase price over fair value of net assets acquired was recorded as goodwill.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The goodwill recorded as a result of the acquisition of Fresh Frozen Foods is expected to be deductible for tax purposes.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Identified intangible assets of $20.0 million consist of customer relationships and trade name.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The customer relationships are amortized using the straight-line method over the estimated useful life of twelve years.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We believe the acquired trade name has the continued ability to generate cash flows indefinitely
 and therefore the trade name has been determined to have an indefinite life.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Goodwill of $8.3 million represents the excess of the purchase price over the estimated fair value assigned to tangible and identifiable intangible assets acquired and liabilities assumed from Fresh Frozen Foods. In accordance with current accounting standards
 the goodwill is not amortized and will be tested for impairment annually in the fourth quarter of our fiscal year.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;See Note 3 &amp;#x201C;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Goodwill
 Trademarks and Other Intangible Assets&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;#x201D; for additional information.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Based on Fresh Frozen Foods&amp;#x2019; financial performance for fiscal 2014
 we concluded the earn-out would not be paid.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Accordingly
 the liability for contingent consideration was adjusted to $0
 which resulted in a decrease in operating expenses of $2.7 million during the year ended December 27
 2014.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Willamette Valley Fruit Company&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;On May 28
 2013
 we enhanced our berry purchase and freezing capabilities by acquiring the berry processing business of Willamette Valley Fruit Company
 LLC
 one of the Pacific Northwest&amp;#x2019;s leading processors of high-quality berry products
 for a cash purchase price of $9.3 million.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;An additional amount of up to $3.0 million may be payable to Willamette Valley Fruit Company as contingent consideration if certain performance thresholds are met during the seven-year period following the closing of the transaction.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Under the terms of the purchase agreement
 we acquired substantially all of the berry processing equipment assets
 including a new Individually Quick Frozen (&amp;#x201C;IQF&amp;#x201D;) tunnel
 and other intellectual property and inventory rights.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We also entered into leases of the land and buildings containing the purchased assets in connection with the transaction.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The amount of net revenues attributable to Willamette Valley Fruit Company included in the consolidated statements of operations since the acquisition date were $14.1 million in fiscal 2013.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We do not allocate certain selling
 general and administrative expenses and therefore
 it is impracticable for us to separately identify earnings of the acquired entity since acquisition.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:02.80%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 12pt&gt;

				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td colspan=2 valign=bottom style=width:13.44%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;text-align:right;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 12pt&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:02.80%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 12pt&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:01.36%;border-top:1pt solid #000000 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;$&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:12.08%;border-top:1pt solid #000000 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;text-align:right; nowrap=nowrap&gt;&lt;div style=float:left&gt;&lt;/div&gt;3
147
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:01.06%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 12pt&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Under the acquisition method of accounting
 the purchase price as shown in the table above is allocated to the tangible and identifiable intangible assets acquired and liabilities assumed based on their estimated fair values.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The excess purchase price over fair value of net assets acquired was recorded as goodwill.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The goodwill recorded as a result of the acquisition of Willamette Valley Fruit Company is expected to be deductible for tax purposes.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The estimated values of current liabilities were based upon their historical costs on the date of acquisition due to their short-term nature.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Identified intangible assets of $3.9 million consist of customer relationships and trade name.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The customer relationships are amortized using the straight-line method over the estimated useful life of ten years.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We believe the acquired trade name has the continued ability to generate cash flows indefinitely
 and therefore the trade name has been determined to have an indefinite life.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Goodwill of $3.1 million represents the excess of the purchase price over the estimated fair value assigned to tangible and identifiable intangible assets acquired and liabilities assumed from Willamette Valley Fruit Company. In accordance with current accounting standards
 the goodwill is not amortized and will be tested for impairment annually in the fourth quarter of our fiscal year.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;See Note 3 &amp;#x201C;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Goodwill
 Trademarks and Other Intangible Assets&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;#x201D; for additional information.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;During the first quarter of 2014 we paid $0.5 million of the contingent consideration upon completion of certain thresholds achieved during the 2013 fiscal period.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We also paid $0.8 million in holdbacks upon expiration of certain indemnification and completion of post-acquisition obligations.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;As of December 27
 2014
 we reduced our estimate of the total earn-out expected to be achieved.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Accordingly
 the liability for contingent consideration was adjusted to $1.6 million
 which resulted in a decrease in operating expenses of $0.3 million during the year ended December 27
 2014.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Consolidated Pro Forma Financial Information&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;The following unaudited pro forma consolidated results of operations (in thousands
 except per share data) assumes the Willamette Valley Fruit Company and Fresh Frozen Foods acquisitions occurred as of the beginning of the earliest period presented.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The unaudited pro forma results include estimates and assumptions regarding increased amortization of intangible assets related to the acquisitions
 increased interest expense related to debt acquired in order to fund the acquisitions and the related tax effects.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The pro forma results are not necessarily indicative of the actual results that would have occurred had the acquisition been completed as of the beginning of each of the periods presented
 nor are they necessarily indicative of future consolidated results.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Pro forma information related to the Sin In A Tin acquisition has not been included as it is not material.&lt;/font&gt;

			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We account for acquisitions using the acquisition method of accounting.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The results of operations of our acquired businesses have been included in our consolidated results from their respective dates of acquisition.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;On September&amp;nbsp;29
 2014
 we acquired the assets and intellectual property of a small boutique frozen desserts business
 Sin In A Tin
 for approximately $160
000 in cash. An additional amount of up to $0.5 million is payable to the seller in the form of an earn-out based on future net revenues from the Sin In A Tin products (see Note 2).&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;On November&amp;nbsp;8
 2013
 we completed our acquisition of Fresh Frozen Foods
 LLC (&amp;#x201C;Fresh Frozen Foods&amp;#x201D;) for a cash purchase price of $38.4 million plus a working capital adjustment of $0.4 million.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;An additional amount of up to $3.0 million could have been payable to Fresh Frozen Foods as contingent consideration in the form of an earn-out based on 2014 performance (see Note 2).&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;On May&amp;nbsp;28
 2013
 we completed our acquisition of the berry processing business of Willamette Valley Fruit Company
 LLC (&amp;#x201C;Willamette Valley Fruit Company&amp;#x201D;) for a cash purchase price of $9.3 million.&amp;nbsp; An additional amount of up to $3.0 million may be payable to Willamette Valley Fruit Company as contingent consideration in the form of an earn-out if certain performance thresholds are met during the seven-year period following the closing of the transaction (see Note 2).&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;On November&amp;nbsp;5
 2012
 we sold our direct-store-delivery (&amp;#x201C;DSD&amp;#x201D;) business for $1.2 million in cash
 which included a network of independently operated and owned service routes and limited fixed assets associated with the DSD business.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We received an additional $0.3 million as a purchase price adjustment for inventory on-hand.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We recognized a net gain of $1.1 million in continuing operations
 as we will continue to indirectly sell our products through this network at a reduced cost and will no longer sell distributed products.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Our sales of distributed products were $2.6 million in fiscal year 2012.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Our DSD business was part of our indulgent specialty snack segment and included a limited number of snack food products purchased and sold through our DSD network in Arizona.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  

		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Cash and Cash Equivalents&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We consider all highly liquid investments purchased with an original maturity of three months or less to be cash equivalents.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;




		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;8.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;;font-size: 10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-indent:0pt;margin-left:0pt;padding:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:3pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;Commitments and Contingencies&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Our future contractual obligations consist principally of long-term debt
 operating leases
 minimum commitments regarding third-party warehouse operations services
 forward purchase agreements and remaining minimum royalty payments due licensors pursuant to brand licensing agreements.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;

		&lt;/p&gt;

 2014
 December&amp;nbsp;28
 2013 and December&amp;nbsp;29
 2012
 the rental expense from operating leases was $2.6 million

		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Purchase agreements&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;In order to mitigate the risks of volatility in commodity markets to which we are exposed
 we have entered into forward purchase agreements with certain suppliers based on market prices
 forward price projections and expected usage levels.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Our purchase commitments for certain ingredients
 packaging materials and energy are generally less than 12 months.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Licensing&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We produce T.G.I. Friday&amp;#x2019;s&amp;#xAE; brand snacks
 Tato Skins&amp;#xAE; brand potato crisps and Boulder Canyon&amp;#xAE; Authentic Foods Rice and Bean snacks utilizing a sheeting and frying process that includes technology that we license from a third party.&amp;nbsp; Pursuant to the license agreement between us and the third party
 we have a royalty-bearing
 exclusive right license to use the technology in the United States
 Canada
 and Mexico until such time the parties mutually agree to terminate the agreement.&amp;nbsp; Even though the patents for this technology expired in December&amp;nbsp;2006
 in consideration for the use of this technology
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of products manufactured utilizing the technology until such termination date.&amp;nbsp; However
 should products substantially similar to Tato Skins&amp;#xAE;
 O&amp;#x2019;Boisies&amp;#xAE; and Pizzarias&amp;#xAE; become available for any reason in the marketplace by any manufacturer other than us which results in a sales decline of 10% or more
 any royalty obligation for the respective products&amp;nbsp;shall cease.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We license the T.G.I. Friday&amp;#x2019;s&amp;#xAE; brand snacks trademark from T.G.I. Friday&amp;#x2019;s Inc. under a license agreement with a term expiring in December 2019.&amp;nbsp; Pursuant to the license agreement
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of T.G.I. Friday&amp;#x2019;s&amp;#xAE; brand snack products and are required to achieve certain minimum sales levels by certain dates during the contract term.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We license the Jamba&amp;#xAE; brand trademark from Jamba Juice Company under a license agreement with a term expiring in 2035.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Pursuant to the license agreement
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of Jamba&amp;#xAE; products
 and are required to achieve certain minimum sales levels by certain dates during the contract term.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We license the Nathan&amp;#x2019;s Famous&amp;#xAE; brand trademark from Nathan&amp;#x2019;s Famous Corporation under a license agreement with a term expiring in 2031.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Pursuant to the license agreement
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of Nathan&amp;#x2019;s Famous&amp;#xAE; products
 and are required to achieve certain minimum sales levels by certain dates during the contract term.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We license the Vidalia&amp;#xAE; brand trademark from Vidalia Brands
 Inc. under a license agreement with a term expiring January 2019.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Pursuant to the license agreement
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of Vidalia&amp;#xAE; brand products during the contract term.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We license the Seattle&amp;#x2019;s Best Coffee&amp;#xAE; brand trademark from Seattle&amp;#x2019;s Best Coffee LLC under a license agreement with a term expiring November 2017
 which automatically extends for a five-year period upon meeting certain minimum sales targets.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Pursuant to the license agreement
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of Seattle&amp;#x2019;s Best Coffee&amp;#xAE;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;brand products during the contract term.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Legal Proceedings&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We are periodically a party to various lawsuits arising in the ordinary course of business.&amp;nbsp; Management believes
 based on discussions with legal counsel
 that the resolution of any such lawsuits
 individually and in the aggregate
&amp;nbsp;will not have a material adverse effect on our financial position or results of operations.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;See Note 12
 &amp;#x201C;Litigation.&amp;#x201D;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  

		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;15.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;;font-size: 10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-indent:0pt;margin-left:0pt;padding:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:3pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;Concentrations of Credit Risk&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We maintain most of our cash with one financial institution.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;As of November&amp;nbsp;1
 2008
 the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (&amp;#x201C;FDIC&amp;#x201D;) introduced the transaction guarantee program which guaranteed non-interest bearing accounts without limit.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The FDIC program is temporary and only offered through participating financial institutions.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Our primary financial institution participated in this program and
 therefore
 all cash balances held with this institution as of December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014 are insured.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Our primary concentration of credit risk is related to certain trade accounts receivable.&amp;nbsp; In the normal course of business
 we extend unsecured credit to our customers.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We investigate a customer&amp;#x2019;s credit worthiness before extending credit.&amp;nbsp; At December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014 and December&amp;nbsp;28
 2013
 three customers accounted for 39% and 35% of accounts receivable
 respectively.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

  
  
  
  
  

		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Principles of Consolidation&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;The consolidated financial statements include the accounts of Inventure Foods
&amp;nbsp;Inc. and all of its wholly owned subsidiaries.&amp;nbsp; All significant intercompany amounts and transactions have been eliminated.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Our fiscal year ends on the last Saturday occurring in the month of December&amp;nbsp;of each calendar year.&amp;nbsp; Accordingly
 the fiscal year end dates result in an additional week of results every five or six years.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Fiscal year 2014 commenced December&amp;nbsp;29
 2013 and ended December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014
 resulting in a 52-week fiscal year.&amp;nbsp; Fiscal year 2013 commenced December&amp;nbsp;30
 2012 ended December&amp;nbsp;28
 2013
 resulting in a 52-week fiscal year.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Fiscal year 2012 commenced January&amp;nbsp;1
 2012 ended December&amp;nbsp;29
 2012
 resulting in a 52-week fiscal year.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;7.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;;font-size: 10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-indent:0pt;margin-left:0pt;padding:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:3pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;Long-Term Debt and Line of Credit&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;In August&amp;nbsp;2014
 we entered into two separate equipment term loans with Banc of America Leasing&amp;nbsp;&amp;amp; Capital LLC; one for $2.6 million to finance equipment to be used at the Company&amp;#x2019;s Rader Farms facility
 and the other for $1.9 million to finance equipment to be used at Willamette Valley Fruit Company.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Both of these equipment term loans accrue interest at a rate of 2.35% and will be repaid over 60 recurring monthly payments commencing September&amp;nbsp;15
 2014.&lt;/font&gt;

 2013
 we entered into a $60.0&amp;nbsp;million senior secured term loan and a new $30.0 million senior secured revolving line of credit with a syndicate of lenders led by U.S. Bank National Association (&amp;#x201C;U.S. Bank&amp;#x201D;)
 pursuant to a Credit Agreement
 a Security Agreement and certain other customary ancillary agreements (the &amp;#x201C;Senior Credit Facility&amp;#x201D;).&amp;nbsp; To facilitate the Senior Credit Facility
 the Company and its wholly owned subsidiaries entered into a Letter Amendment Agreement
 dated as of November&amp;nbsp;8
 2013
 with U.S. Bank (the &amp;#x201C;Letter Amendment&amp;#x201D;).&amp;nbsp; The Letter Amendment reconciled the terms of the Senior Credit Facility with the terms of the Loan and Security Agreement and that certain Loan Agreement (term loan)
 dated as of November&amp;nbsp;30
 2006
 by and between the Company&amp;#x2019;s wholly owned subsidiary
 La Cometa Properties
&amp;nbsp;Inc.
 and U.S. Bank.&lt;/font&gt;

 plus the LIBOR Rate Margin (as defined in the revolving credit facility note) as adjusted.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;&gt;Bluffton
&amp;nbsp;Indiana mortgage loan due December&amp;nbsp;2016; interest rate at 30 day LIBOR&amp;nbsp;plus 165 basis points
 fixed through a swap agreement to 6.85%; collateralized by land and a building in Bluffton
&amp;nbsp;Indiana.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

			&lt;p style=font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;&gt;

			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;&gt;Lynden
 Washington real estate term loan due July&amp;nbsp;2017; interest at LIBOR plus 165 basis&amp;nbsp;points; fixed through a swap agreement to 4.28%; secured by a leasehold interest in the real property in Lynden
 Washington.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;&gt;As is customary in such financings
 U.S. Bank
 on behalf of the syndicate of lenders
 may terminate the syndicate&amp;#x2019;s commitments
 accelerate the repayment of amounts outstanding and exercise other remedies upon the occurrence of an event of default (as defined in the Senior Credit Facility)
 subject
 in certain instances
 to the expiration of an applicable cure period.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Senior Credit Facility requires us to maintain compliance with certain financial covenants
 including a minimum fixed charge coverage ratio and a leverage ratio.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;At December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014
 we were in compliance with all of the financial covenants.&lt;/font&gt;

				&lt;/td&gt;

					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;

				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:03.76%;background-color: #CCEEFF;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;

					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;&gt;$&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:16.60%;border-top:1pt solid #000000 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #CCEEFF;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;text-align:right; nowrap=nowrap&gt;&lt;div style=float:left&gt;&lt;/div&gt;(764
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:01.42%;background-color: #CCEEFF;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;&gt;)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;&gt;Interest Rate Swaps&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;&gt;To manage exposure to changing interest rates
 we selectively enter into interest rate swap agreements.&amp;nbsp; Our interest rate swaps qualify for and are designated as cash flow hedges.&amp;nbsp; Changes in the fair value of a swap that is highly effective and that is designated and qualifies as a cash flow hedge to the extent that the hedge is effective
 are recorded in other comprehensive income.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;&gt;We entered into an interest rate swap in 2006 to convert the interest rate of the mortgage to purchase the Bluffton
&amp;nbsp;Indiana plant from the contractual rate of 30 day LIBOR plus 165 basis points to a fixed rate of 6.85%.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The swap has a fixed pay-rate of 6.85% and a notional value of approximately $1.8 million and $1.9 million at December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014 and December&amp;nbsp;28
 2013
 respectively
 and expires in December&amp;nbsp;2016.&amp;nbsp; We evaluate the effectiveness of the hedge on a quarterly basis and
 at December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014
 the hedge is highly effective.&amp;nbsp; The interest rate swap had a fair value of approximately $155
000 and $240
000 at December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014 and December&amp;nbsp;28
 2013
 respectively
 which were recorded as a liability on the accompanying Consolidated Balance Sheets.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The swap value was determined in accordance with the fair value measurement guidance discussed earlier using Level 2 observable inputs and approximates the loss that would have been realized if the contract had been settled at the end of the fiscal period.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;&gt;We entered into another interest rate swap in January&amp;nbsp;2008 to effectively convert the interest rate on the real estate term loan to a fixed rate of 4.28%.&amp;nbsp; The interest rate swap is structured with decreasing notional values to match the expected pay down of the debt.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The notional value of the swap was $2.6 million and $2.8 million at December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014 and December&amp;nbsp;28
 2013
 respectively.&amp;nbsp; The interest rate swap is accounted for as a cash flow hedge derivative and expires in July&amp;nbsp;2017.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The interest rate swap had fair value of approximately $194
000 and $286
000 at December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014 and December&amp;nbsp;28
 2013
 respectively
 which were recorded as a liability on the accompanying Consolidated Balance Sheet.&amp;nbsp; This value was determined in accordance with the fair value measurement guidance discussed earlier using Level 2 observable inputs and approximates the loss that would have been realized if the contract had been settled at the end of the fiscal period.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  

		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Derivative Financial Instruments&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We utilize interest rate swaps in the management of our variable interest rate exposure and do not enter into derivatives for trading purposes.&amp;nbsp; All derivatives are measured at fair value.&amp;nbsp; Our interest rate swaps are classified as cash flow hedges.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  

		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Earnings Per Common Share&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Basic earnings per common share is computed by dividing net income by the weighted average number of shares of Common Stock outstanding during the period.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Diluted earnings per share is calculated by including all dilutive common shares such as stock options and restricted stock.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;For the years ended December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014
 December&amp;nbsp;28
 2013 and December&amp;nbsp;29
 2012 options to purchase 26
306
 291
571 and 281
017 shares of our common stock
 respectively
 were excluded from the calculation of diluted earnings per share because their effects were antidilutive.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;These exclusions were made because the options&amp;#x2019; exercise prices were greater than the average market price of our Common Stock for those periods.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Exercises of outstanding stock options or warrants are assumed to occur for purposes of calculating diluted earnings per share for periods in which their effect would not be anti-dilutive.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Earnings per common share was computed as follows for the years ended December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014
 December&amp;nbsp;28
 2013 and December&amp;nbsp;29
 2012 (in thousands
 except per share data):&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;

		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;The following table summarizes the valuation of our assets and liabilities measured at fair value on a recurring basis (in thousands) at the respective dates set forth below:&lt;/font&gt;

			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;

				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:13.06%;border-top:1pt solid #000000 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;text-align:right; nowrap=nowrap&gt;&lt;div style=float:left&gt;&lt;/div&gt;1

				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:01.50%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 12pt&gt;

		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

  
  
  
  

		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Fair Value of Financial Instruments&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:28.8pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Fair value is defined as the price that would be received to sell an asset or paid to transfer a liability (i.e.
 the &amp;#x201C;exit price&amp;#x201D;) in an orderly transaction between market participants at the measurement date.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;W&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;e classify our investments based upon an established fair value hierarchy that prioritizes the inputs to valuation techniques used to measure fair value.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The hierarchy gives the highest priority to unadjusted quoted prices in active markets for identical assets or liabilities (Level 1 measurement) and the lowest priority to unobservable inputs (Level 3 measurement).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The three levels of the fair value hierarchy are described as follows:&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:28.8pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;div style=width:100%&gt;&lt;table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 style=border-collapse:collapse;margin-left:36pt;&gt;
			&lt;tr&gt;
				&lt;td valign=top style=width:10.00%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10pt;line-height:106.67%;text-indent: -10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;Level 1&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=top style=width:90.00%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Unadjusted quoted prices in active markets that are accessible at the measurement date for identical
 unrestricted assets or liabilities.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;tr&gt;
				&lt;td valign=top style=width:10.00%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10pt;line-height:106.67%;text-indent: -10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=top style=width:90.00%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 12pt&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;tr&gt;
				&lt;td valign=top style=width:10.00%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10pt;line-height:106.67%;text-indent: -10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;Level 2&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=top style=width:90.00%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Quoted prices in markets that are not considered to be active or financial instruments without quoted market prices
 but for which all significant inputs are observable
 either directly or indirectly.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;tr&gt;
				&lt;td valign=top style=width:10.00%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10pt;line-height:106.67%;text-indent: -10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=top style=width:90.00%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 12pt&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;tr&gt;
				&lt;td valign=top style=width:10.00%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10pt;line-height:106.67%;text-indent: -10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;Level 3&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=top style=width:90.00%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Prices or valuations that require inputs that are both significant to the fair value measurement and unobservable.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:28.8pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;A financial instrument&amp;#x2019;s level within the fair value hierarchy is based on the lowest level of any input that is significant to the fair value measurement.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:28.8pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;At December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014 and December&amp;nbsp;28
 2013
 the carrying value of cash
 accounts receivable
 accounts payable and accrued liabilities approximate fair values since they are short term in nature.&amp;nbsp; The carrying value of the long-term debt approximates fair value based on the borrowing rates currently available to us for long-term borrowings with similar terms. The following table summarizes the valuation of our assets and liabilities measured at fair value on a recurring basis (in thousands) at the respective dates set forth below:&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;div style=width:100%&gt;&lt;table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 style=border-collapse:collapse;width: 100.00%;margin-left:0pt;&gt;
			&lt;tr&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:19.00%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 8pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:8pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:02.00%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;text-align:center;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 12pt&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:06.00%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;text-align:center;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 12pt&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:02.00%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;text-align:center;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 12pt&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td colspan=8 valign=bottom style=width:34.00%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;text-align:center;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 8pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:8pt;&gt;December&amp;nbsp;27
&amp;nbsp;2014&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:02.00%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;text-align:center;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 12pt&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td colspan=8 valign=bottom style=width:34.00%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;text-align:center;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 8pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:8pt;&gt;December&amp;nbsp;28
&amp;nbsp;2013&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:01.00%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;text-align:center;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 12pt&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;tr&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:19.00%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;padding:0pt;&gt;

		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Considerable judgment is required in interpreting market data to develop the estimate of fair value of our derivative instruments.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Accordingly
 the estimate may not be indicative of the amounts that we could realize in a current market exchange.&amp;nbsp; The use of different market assumptions or valuation methodologies could have a material effect on the estimated fair value amounts.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;The Company&amp;#x2019;s non-qualified deferred compensation plan assets consist of money market and mutual funds invested in domestic and international marketable securities that are directly observable in active markets.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;The fair value measurement of the earn-out contingent consideration obligation relates to the acquisitions of Sin In A Tin in September&amp;nbsp;2014
 Willamette Valley Fruit Company in May&amp;nbsp;2013 and Fresh Frozen Foods in November&amp;nbsp;2013
 and is included in accrued liabilities and other long-term liabilities in the consolidated balance sheets.&amp;nbsp; The fair value measurement is based upon significant inputs not observable in the market.&amp;nbsp; Changes in the value of the obligation are recorded as income or expense in our consolidated statements of income.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;To determine the fair value
 we valued the contingent consideration liability based on the expected probability weighted earn-out payments corresponding to the performance thresholds agreed to under the applicable purchase agreements.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The expected earn-out payments were then present valued by applying a discount rate that captures a market participants view of the risk associated with the expected earn-out payments.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;During the year ended December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014
 we reduced the value of the contingent consideration related to the Fresh Frozen Foods acquisition to zero due to forecasted reduction in estimated achievement of targets
 and we reduced the value of the contingent consideration related to the Willamette Valley Fruit Company acquisition by $0.3 million based on a reduction in our estimate of the total earn-out expected to be achieved.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;A summary of the activity of the fair value of the measurements using unobservable inputs (Level 3 Liabilities) for the year ended December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014
 is as follows (in thousands):&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;div style=width:100%&gt;&lt;table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 style=border-collapse:collapse;width: 66.00%;margin-left:90pt;&gt;
			&lt;tr&gt;

		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Goodwill and trademarks are reviewed for impairment annually in the fourth fiscal quarter
 or more frequently if impairment indicators arise.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Goodwill is required to be tested for impairment between the annual tests if an event occurs or circumstances change that more-likely-than-not reduces the fair value of a reporting unit below its carrying value.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Intangible assets with indefinite lives are required to be tested for impairment between the annual tests if an event occurs or circumstances change indicating that the asset might be impaired.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;No impairments were determined through our testing for the year ended December 27
 2014.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Intangible Assets&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Goodwill and trademarks are reviewed for impairment annually or more frequently if impairment indicators arise.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Goodwill
 by reporting unit
 is required to be tested for impairment between the annual tests if an event occurs or circumstances change that more-likely-than-not reduces the fair value of a reporting unit below its carrying value.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We have concluded from our annual impairment testing performed in December&amp;nbsp;that neither of our two reporting units was at risk of failing the impairment test in the near term
 and we believe that there are no known risks for that conclusion to change at either of our reporting units.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Intangible assets with indefinite lives are required to be tested for impairment between the annual tests if an event occurs or circumstances change indicating that the asset might be impaired.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Amortizable intangible assets are amortized using the straight-line method over their estimated useful lives
 which is the estimated period over which economic benefits are expected to be provided.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Management believes that each of our trademarks has the continued ability to generate cash flows indefinitely.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Therefore
 each of our trademarks has been determined to have an indefinite life.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Management&amp;#x2019;s determination that our trademarks have indefinite lives includes an evaluation of historical cash flows and projected cash flows for each of these trademarks.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;In addition
 there are no legal
 regulatory
 contractual
 economic or other factors to limit the useful life of these trademarks.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Management intends to renew each of these trademarks
 which can be accomplished at little cost.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;See Note 3 &amp;#x201C;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Goodwill
 Trademarks and Other Intangible Assets&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;#x201D; for additional information.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;line-height:normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;10&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Income Taxes&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;

		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;The provision for income taxes consisted of the following for the years ended December 27
 2014
